As an introverted creative person who values privacy and is an independent entrepreneur, running a business shouldn't feel so awkward, but sometimes it does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to deal with large (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. To advertise here, you have to follow the algorithm, share your personality charm. Get verified on that platform, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own videos, and respond immediately. Videos, videos, and more videos.
1/3
This year is a year of transformation for me.
I don't want to give my money, data, and energy to large tech companies anymore, and I don't want to listen to mentors who only suggest a single, one-size-fits-all extroverted solution for everyone. I'm exploring new business models and working to overcome my long-held belief that there's only one way to succeed.
Wish me luck!
The first step has been taken.
I've exited FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and cancelled my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, and I feel great about it.
To better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service and will be migrating my business to it over the next few weeks.
I've moved my MX records to Proton and now have complete SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
