Website: check out @user5. It looks easy to use, has a beautiful interface, and it's open-source. I plan to migrate one of my websites to it before the next renewal.
Signal: take a look at cal.com. It's an open-source calendar service that integrates video call features from Element, JITSI, etc. It also supports Signal, but I haven't tested yet if it's just for messaging or for video calls.
I can recommend @user6. End-to-end encrypted, decentralized, and open-source.
